This paper is about abstractive summarization, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses neural models and reinforcement learning, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper involves selecting salient sentences and compressing information, which are tasks related to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper uses entity information to generate summaries, which is a task related to named entity recognition (cs.NE).
